A music video for "Por Debajo de la Mesa" was filmed in [[New York City]] which features Miguel performing at the [[Rainbow Room]] with the video being shot in [[black-and-white]].<ref>{{cite video| people = Miguel, Luis (performer)| title = Por Debajo de la Mesa|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=giAE7Yz7gHI | medium = Television| publisher = [[Warner Music|Warner Music Mexico]]| location = New York City| date = 1997 }}</ref> The song was included on his greatest hits album ''[[Mis Boleros Favoritos]]'' (2002) and ''[[Grandes <U+00C9>xitos (Luis Miguel album)| Grandes <U+00C9>xitos]]'' (2005).<ref>{{cite web|title=Por Debajo de la Mesa&nbsp;<U+2014> Luis Miguel|url=http://www.allmusic.com/song/por-debajo-de-la-mesa-mt0035008714s|accessdate=2014-01-03|work=Allmusic|publisher=Rovi Corporation}}</ref> A live version of the song was included on his album ''[[Vivo (Luis Miguel album)|Vivo]]'' (2000) as part of the "''Romances'' Medley".<ref>{{cite web|title=Vivo&nbsp;<U+2014> Overview|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/vivo-mw0000619848|accessdate=2014-01-03|work=Allmusic|publisher=Rovi Corporation}}</ref>

==Release and reception==
"Por Debajo de la Mesa" serviced to radio stations across Latin America on July 15, 1997.<ref>{{cite news |title= Llega a todo el mundo 'Por Debajo de la Mesa|first=Carlos |last= Meraz|url=http://busquedas.gruporeforma.com/reforma/Pages/BuscaImpresa.aspx|newspaper= El Norte|publisher=Grupo Reforma|date= 1997-07-15|accessdate=2011-03-28|language=Spanish}}{{subscription required}}</ref> In the United States, the song debuted at number two on the [[Hot Latin Songs|''Billboard'' Hot Latin Songs]] chart on the week of August 2, 1997.<ref>{{cite web |title=Top Latin Songs&nbsp;<U+2014> Week of August 7, 1997 |work=Billboard |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=1997-08-02 |url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/1997-08-02/latin-songs |accessdate=2011-04-15 }}</ref> Six weeks later, it peaked at number one on the chart where and remained on the position for four weeks.<ref>{{cite web |title=Top Latin Songs&nbsp;<U+2014> Week of September 6, 1997 |work=Billboard |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=1997-09-07  |url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/1997-09-06/latin-songs |accessdate=2009-04-15 }}</ref> "Por Debajo de la Mesa" ended 1997 as the eighth best-performing Latin single of the year in the United States.<ref name="yearend1997"/> The track also peaked at number one on the [[Latin Pop Songs|''Billboard'' Latin Pop Songs]] chart where it spent five weeks on top of the chart and was the best-performing Latin pop song of the year in the country.<ref>{{cite web |title= Latin Pop Songs&nbsp;<U+2014> Week of August 30, 1997 |work=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media |date=1997-08-30|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/1997-08-30/latin-pop-songs |accessdate=2014-01-01}}</ref><ref name="yearend1997"/>

Despite giving ''Romances'' a positive review, ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' editor [[Achy Obejas]] called "Por Debajo de la Mesa" a "lame" song and cited it as one of the songs where Miguel beginning is "to slip" on his ballad recordings.<ref name="Obejas">{{cite web| last =  Obejas| first = Achy| date = 1997-10-03|title= Music. Album Reviews <U+2013> Luis Miguel Romances|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1997-10-03/entertainment/9710030393_1_armando-manzanero-songs-oldies|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|accessdate=2011-02-19}}</ref> It received a nomination for [[Lo Nuestro Award for Pop Song of the Year|Pop Song of the Year]] at the [[Premio Lo Nuestro 1998|Lo Nuestro Awards of 1998]], losing to "Si Tu Supieras" by [[Alejandro Fern<U+00E1>ndez]].<ref name="univision-lonuestro-1998">{{cite news|url=http://wvw.nacion.com/viva/1998/abril/03/espec9.html|title=Premios Lo Nuestro: Los galardones a la m<U+00FA>sica latina ser<U+00E1>n entregados en mayo pr<U+00F3>ximo||last=Barquero|first=Christopher|language=Spanish|work=[[La Naci<U+00F3>n (San Jos<U+00E9>)|La Naci<U+00F3>n]]|publisher=Grupo Naci<U+00F3>n GN, S.A.|year=1998|accessdate=2013-06-14}}</ref><ref name="Winners2">{{cite web |url=http://archivo.univision.com/content/content.jhtml?cid=490998|title=Lo Nuestro 1998 <U+2013> Historia |language=Spanish |work=[[Univision]] |publisher=Univision Communications, Inc |accessdate=2013-06-14 |year=1998}}</ref> Manzanero was given a [[Broadcast Music, Inc.|BMI]] Latin Award for composition of the song due to it being one of the best-performing Latin songs of the year.<ref>{{cite web|title=BMI Latin Awards: 1999|url=http://www.bmi.com/news/entry/533568|date=1999-01-01|publisher=[[Broadcast Music, Inc.]]|accessdate=2011-02-19}}</ref>

