==Other recordings==
Manzanero has sung "Por Debajo de la Mesa" as a duet Peruvian musician [[Tania Libertad]] on the duo's studio album ''Manzanero y la Libertad'' (1998) and with [[Chano Dom<U+00ED>nguez]] and Carmen Paris on Manazero's album ''Duetos 2'' (2002).<ref>{{cite web|title=Manzanero y la Libertad&nbsp;<U+2014> Overview|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/manzanero-y-la-libertad-mw0000051683|accessdate=2014-01-03|work=Allmusic|publisher=Rovi Corporation}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Duetos 2&nbsp;<U+2014> Overview|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/duetos-2-mw0000663282|accessdate=2014-01-03|work=Allmusic|publisher=Rovi Corporation}}</ref> He also performed the song in a concert with Argentine pianist [[Ra<U+00FA>l di Blasio]] in 1999 which was included on the latter's live album ''Bohemia, Vol.2'' (2000) and also performed the song live with fellow Mexican singer [[Susana Zabaleta]] on their album ''De la A a la Z'' (2006).<ref>{{cite web|title=Bohemia, Vol. 2&nbsp;<U+2014> Overview|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/bohemia-vol-2-mw0000068860|accessdate=2014-01-03|work=Allmusic|publisher=Rovi Corporation}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=De la A a la Z [DVD]&nbsp;<U+2014> Overview|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/de-la-a-a-la-z-dvd-mw0001222879|accessdate=2014-01-03|work=Allmusic|publisher=Rovi Corporation}}</ref>

